# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you shouldn't ignore these files, but for a specific project, it's fine.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you want to keep dependencies as tight as possible,
#   you might want to ignore it. 
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/dependency/#commit-the-lockfile
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/frenzycry/pdm
__pypackages__/

